.TH "ubi_start_update" 9 "ubi_start_update" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ubi_start_update \- start volume update.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ubi_start_update
.BI "(struct ubi_device *ubi "  ","
.BI "struct ubi_volume *vol "  ","
.BI "long long bytes "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ubi" 12
UBI device description object
.IP "vol" 12
volume description object
.IP "bytes" 12
update bytes
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function starts volume update operation. If \fIbytes\fP is zero, the volume
is just wiped out. Returns zero in case of success and a negative error code
in case of failure.
